{"word":"ἐμπήγνυμι","slug":"ἐμπήγνυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐμπήγνυμι</b></el> <el>(and <el>-ύω</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-πήξω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐν'><el>ἐν</el></a>\n<p/><i>to fix</i> or <i>plant in</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> and plup. <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>to be fixed</i> or <i>stuck in, to stick in</i>, <el>τινί</el> or <el>ἔν τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/>"}]}